Git-1.6.3.2-preview20090608.exe

Install it and include it in your path

C:\Johan\Ruby\Rails\yoyaku>git --version
git version 1.6.3.2.1299.gee46c

C:\Johan\Ruby\Rails\yoyaku>git config --global user.name "Johan Sveholm"
fatal: $HOME not set

C:\Documents and Settings\Johan>set home
HOMEDRIVE=C:
HOMEPATH=\Documents and Settings\Johan

You can set it yourself to where you want git to store the .gitconfig
file. Do this in Settings->System->Advanced->Environment Variables,
section User variables. You can set it to %HOMEDRIVE%%HOMEPATH%  in order
point it somewhere below C:\Documents and Settings.

C:\Documents and Settings\Johan>set home
HOME=C:\Documents and Settings\Johan
HOMEDRIVE=C:
HOMEPATH=\Documents and Settings\Johan

C:\Johan\Ruby\Rails\yoyaku>git config --global user.name "Johan Sveholm"
